The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | NTPC in renewable energy pact
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       NTPC in renewable energy pact
                            
	New Delhi, Aug. 5 (PTI): State-run NTPC Ltd, Asian Development Bank, GE Energy Financial Services, Kyushu Electric Power Co and Brookfield Renewable Power will form a joint venture company for generating renewable power.        
	The companies today signed a memorandum of understanding (MoU) to form a joint venture. NTPC will hold a 40 per cent stake in the company, while the remaining will be equally shared among the other entities.        
	The joint venture plans to produce 500MW of renewable power. The chairman of the new entity will be nominated by NTPC.        
	Import plans        
	NTPC plans to import eight million tonnes of coal in the current fiscal to bridge the shortfall in the total requirement of 125 million tonnes.        
	The company, which has an installed capacity of 29,000 MW, plans to add 22,000 MW in the Eleventh Plan (2007-12) and another 25,000 MW by 2017.                                                                                                                                      
